  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Efficient, adaptive energy stable schemes for the incompressible Cahn–Hilliard Navier–Stokes phase-field models</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2016-03-01</subfield>
    <subfield code="t">published</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="300" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">17</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this paper we develop a fully adaptive energy stable scheme for Cahn–Hilliard Navier–Stokes system, which is a phase-field model for two-phase incompressible flows, consisting a Cahn–Hilliard-type diffusion equation and a Navier–Stokes equation. This scheme, which is decoupled and unconditionally energy stable based on stabilization, involves adaptive mesh, adaptive time and a nonlinear multigrid finite difference method. Numerical experiments are carried out to validate the scheme for problems with matched density and non-matched density, and also demonstrate that CPU time can be significantly reduced with our adaptive approach.</subfield>
    <subfield code="9">Elsevier</subfield>
  </datafield>
